OL,5, The minimum wage is to increase by more
OL,6, than a pound to #11.44 per hour from   
OL,7, April next year.                       
OL,9,FThe minimum wage, known officially as  
OL,10,Fthe National Living Wage, is currently 
OL,11,F#10.42 an hour for workers over 23.    
OL,13,FBut Chancellor Jeremy Hunt has decided 
OL,14,Fthe rate will also apply to 21 and     
OL,15,F22-year-olds for the first time.       
OL,17,FIt means a full-time worker aged 23 on 
OL,18,Fthe wage would receive a rise worth    
OL,19,F#1,800 a year. A 21-year-old would see 
OL,20,Fan effective #2,300 annual rise.       
